stylometry: Transportation problems are problems where you have a point A and point B.  Point A being the origin and B being the destination.  In transportation problems your shipping something from A to B.  Transshipment problems are more complex because you have a a middle location between point A and point B.  In transportation and transhipment problems you have nodes, arcs and flows.  The nodes being the location, arcs being the pathway, and the flows which means how much is being shipped over the arc.  An example of a transhipment problem was the warehouse model we did.  From point A we shipped the product to the warehouse(middle location) and then it was shipped to point B known as the location.
